Sentence: She doesn't like cold weather.
She : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "like"
doesn't : auxiliary verb "do" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: does not), third person singular, present tense, indicates negative aspect
like : verb, base form, main verb of the sentence
cold : adjective, modifies the noun "weather"
weather : noun, singular, direct object of the verb "like"

Sentence: They didn't finish the project yesterday.
They : pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "finish"
didn't : auxiliary verb "do" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: did not), past tense, indicates negative aspect
finish : verb, base form, main verb of the sentence
the : definite article, modifies the noun "project"
project : noun, singular, direct object of the verb "finish"
yesterday : adverb of time, modifies the verb phrase "didn't finish"

Sentence: I am not ready for the meeting.
I : pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb "am"
am : auxiliary verb "be", first person singular, present tense
not : adverb, negation particle, modifies the adjective "ready"
ready : adjective, subject complement describing "I"
for : preposition, introduces the prepositional phrase
the : definite article, modifies the noun "meeting"
meeting : noun, singular, object of the preposition "for"

Sentence: We aren't going to the party tonight.
We : pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb "going"
aren't : auxiliary verb "be" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: are not), first person plural, present tense, indicates negative aspect
going : verb, present participle, part of the present continuous tense
to : preposition, indicates direction
the : definite article, modifies the noun "party"
party : noun, singular, object of the preposition "to"
tonight : adverb of time, modifies the verb phrase "aren't going"

Sentence: He hasn't seen that movie yet.
He : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "seen"
hasn't : auxiliary verb "have" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: has not), third person singular, present perfect tense, indicates negative aspect
seen : verb, past participle, main verb in present perfect construction
that : demonstrative adjective, modifies the noun "movie"
movie : noun, singular, direct object of the verb "seen"
yet : adverb, indicates time up to now, used with negative sentences

Sentence: You can't swim in this pool.
You : pronoun, second person, subject of the verb "swim"
can't : modal auxiliary verb "can" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: cannot), indicates inability or prohibition
swim : verb, base form, main verb of the sentence
in : preposition, indicates location
this : demonstrative adjective, modifies the noun "pool"
pool : noun, singular, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: It won't rain tomorrow morning.
It : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "rain"
won't : modal auxiliary verb "will" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: will not), future tense, indicates negative prediction
rain : verb, base form, main verb of the sentence
tomorrow : adverb of time, modifies the verb phrase "won't rain"
morning : noun, singular, specifies the time of day

Sentence: They don't live in this city anymore.
They : pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "live"
don't : auxiliary verb "do" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: do not), first/second/third person plural, present tense, indicates negative aspect
live : verb, base form, main verb of the sentence
in : preposition, indicates location
this : demonstrative adjective, modifies the noun "city"
city : noun, singular, object of the preposition "in"
anymore : adverb, indicates that a previous situation no longer exists

Sentence: Sarah isn't working at the bank currently.
Sarah : proper noun, singular, subject of the verb "working"
isn't : auxiliary verb "be" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: is not), third person singular, present tense, indicates negative aspect
working : verb, present participle, part of the present continuous tense
at : preposition, indicates location
the : definite article, modifies the noun "bank"
bank : noun, singular, object of the preposition "at"
currently : adverb of time, modifies the verb phrase "isn't working"

Sentence: We haven't received the package yet.
We : pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb "received"
haven't : auxiliary verb "have" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: have not), first person plural, present perfect tense, indicates negative aspect
received : verb, past participle, main verb in present perfect construction
the : definite article, modifies the noun "package"
package : noun, singular, direct object of the verb "received"
yet : adverb, indicates time up to now, used with negative sentences

Sentence: He didn't call me last night.
He : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "call"
didn't : auxiliary verb "do" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: did not), past tense, indicates negative aspect
call : verb, base form, main verb of the sentence
me : pronoun, first person singular, indirect object of the verb "call"
last : adjective, modifies the noun "night"
night : noun, singular, adverbial phrase indicating time

Sentence: You aren't listening to the instructions.
You : pronoun, second person, subject of the verb "listening"
aren't : auxiliary verb "be" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: are not), second person, present tense, indicates negative aspect
listening : verb, present participle, part of the present continuous tense
to : preposition, connects the verb to the object
the : definite article, modifies the noun "instructions"
instructions : noun, plural, object of the preposition "to"

Sentence: I don't understand this question.
I : pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb "understand"
don't : auxiliary verb "do" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: do not), first person singular, present tense, indicates negative aspect
understand : verb, base form, main verb of the sentence
this : demonstrative adjective, modifies the noun "question"
question : noun, singular, direct object of the verb "understand"

Sentence: The dog doesn't bark at strangers.
The : definite article, modifies the noun "dog"
dog : noun, singular, subject of the verb "bark"
doesn't : auxiliary verb "do" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: does not), third person singular, present tense, indicates negative aspect
bark : verb, base form, main verb of the sentence
at : preposition, indicates direction or target
strangers : noun, plural, object of the preposition "at"

Sentence: She won't accept the offer today.
She : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "accept"
won't : modal auxiliary verb "will" + negation "not", contracted form (full form: will not), future tense, indicates negative refusal
accept : verb, base form, main verb of the sentence
the : definite article, modifies the noun "offer"
offer : noun, singular, direct object of the verb "accept"
today : adverb of time, modifies the verb phrase "won't accept"
